  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-PROV-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This synthetic adversarial package introduces a broken provenance chain: an intermediate ValidationSupportResult node is reachable from the Claim provenance scope but carries no upstream prov:wasDerivedFrom, prov:wasGeneratedBy, or prov:used edge, and is not marked uofa:isFoundationalEvidence true. Its description states 'derived from prior experimental work' without an IRI link, making the orphan plausible on casual review.",
